<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-02T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-02T17:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/4305: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-02T17:00:00-05:00">September 2, 1941—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>161. Haitian Government has decided to pay one-third interest coupons
                            deferred April 1st and full payment coupons due October 1st.</p>
                        <p>Whenever you obtain the formal notice I respectfully suggest that you
                            assist Haitian Government to obtain proper publicity.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>